{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Renamed files appear in their own category and are not also counted as a deletion plus an addition.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary is the real git/CLI boundary: rename detection comes from actual repository state and git status/diff rename semantics. A unit test of classification logic can miss real handoff mismatches (e.g., parsing real rename records, path delimiters, similarity markers). Integration is rejected because behavior text requires true repository analysis, and MOCK-HIDE applies if git output is stubbed.","test_description":"Create a temporary real git repo, commit a file, rename it, run the CLI as a subprocess, and assert report has rename count/paths only (no added/deleted entries for that file).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Diffs that include binary files do not cause the tool to crash; binary files are counted in the output.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA is explicit: behavior depends on real git diff behavior for binary blobs and real subprocess/stdout handling. Mocked diff text can hide decode/crash issues that occur only with actual binary content and git output formats.","test_description":"In a real temp git repo, add/modify a binary file (e.g., random bytes), run CLI subprocess over the change set, assert non-zero binary count and successful exit without traceback.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.87,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Running the tool on a repository that has no commits yet produces an empty report rather than an error.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure is tied to real git no-commit state and command exit/status behavior (e.g., HEAD missing). Unit